<Base title="projects · n0t.space">
  <h1>projects</h1>
  <p>Writeups and longer-form project pages.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="https://news.n0t.space">news.n0t.space</a></strong> - small cron job that aggregates daily news so I can keep up without doomscrolling.</li>
    <li id="mutemotion">
      <strong>MuteMotion</strong> - real-time, gyroscope-synced visual overlay that fights motion sickness on handheld gaming consoles (Steam Deck first). Core/Shim architecture: a platform-agnostic C++ engine behind a stable C ABI (the algorithm, treated as a black box) plus a SteamOS Python plugin under Decky Loader (the body). Rendered through a Canvas 2D path inside Decky's CEF webview and a native python-xlib overlay via the GAMESCOPE_EXTERNAL_OVERLAY atom. Validated with a small HCI study. Shim source at <a href="https://github.com/MuteMotion-Tech/MuteMotion-SteamDeck-Shim">MuteMotion-Tech/MuteMotion-SteamDeck-Shim</a>.
      <br /><br />
      <strong>MuteMotion PCVR</strong> - distributed adaptation of the same comfort core for PC-based VR. Three independent processes across two trust zones: a C++ overlay daemon (Raylib + OpenVR, 90 FPS critically-damped spring physics with washout filter and integrator clamp) and a PySide6 control panel on the user's machine, plus a Flask verification service running in an LXC on a self-hosted Proxmox host, exposed publicly via Cloudflare Tunnel at <a href="https://mutemotion.n0t.space">mutemotion.n0t.space</a>. Privacy-by-design identity: locally-generated UUIDs, no PII, no exposed origin IP. Cosmetic skin unlock flow as the architectural vehicle for distributed-systems concepts (client-server identity, persistent state, graceful network-failure degradation). Validated end-to-end on Quest 2 over Air Link. Public writeup pending.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Homelab</strong> - bridge-type architecture: hypervisor host with many VMs (Proxmox-class), travel-router fleet, multi-zone segmentation, Wazuh for telemetry. Writeups focus on the patterns, not the brand list.</li>
    <li><strong>PHLIPPED lab</strong> - see <a href="/phlipped/">phlipped</a>.</li>
  </ul>
</Base>
